  "text": "Two independent reviewers (SG and AT) assessed the methods used by the various studies to document bacterial causes of CAP and possible bias, adapting an algorithm published by Gentile et al. [CITATION_1] , derived from the STROBE (Strengthening the Reporting of Observational studies in Epidemiology) checklist of essential items [CITATION_2] . The case definitions for each study are presented in Table S1 . Methods for selecting the study participants, the methods for measuring the bacterial pathogens' prevalence and methods to control confounding factors were graded from low to high risk of bias (Table S2 ). Disagreements were resolved by consensus.",
